"9:113:8" : {s: 9, a: 113, w: 8, r: "شرك", t: "لِلْمُشْرِكِينَ", l: "مُشْرِك", lc: 44, tl: "lil'mush'rikīna", lb: "মুশরিক, যে আল্লাহর সাথে অংশীদার সাব্যস্ত করে, শিরককারী, অংশীদার স্থাপনকারী",e: "for the polytheists", b: "মুশরিকদের", i: "bagi orang-orang musyrik", f: 3, rm: "to be a companion, be sharer/partner. shirkun - share, participation, polytheism, idolatry, making associate/partner with Allah. shariik (pl. shurakaa) - associate, partner, sharer. Nouns of the second declension when followed by the affixed pronouns take the three inflexions thus shurakaa, shurakaai, shurakaaa. shaarak (vb. 3) - to share with. ashraka (vb. 4) - to make a sharer or associate, give companions (e.g. to God), be a polytheist or idolater. ashraktumuuni - you associated me as partner. mushrik - one who gives associate to God, polytheist. mushtarikun (vb. 8) - one who partakes or shares.", ag: "لام الجر وال التعريف وأسم فاعل", eg: "Preposition lām and Determiner al and Noun Active participle", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "ACT_PCPL", qual: "GEN", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "أَشْرَكَ،شُرَكَآءُ،شُرَكَٰٓؤُا۟،يُشْرِكُ"},
